Biggest Mistakes to Avoid


Using Opus for everyday coding — wastes time/cost for no real quality gain on simple tasks.
Leaving effort on High/Max all the time — slower responses for routine work that doesn't need it.
Using Haiku for genuinely hard problems — you'll get a shallow answer and have to redo it anyway.
Not escalating when stuck — if Sonnet's answer feels incomplete on a hard problem, switch to Opus or raise effort rather than re-asking the same way.



Final Recommendation

If you could only pick ONE model + ONE effort level: Sonnet 5 at Standard effort.

As an occasional-use student focused on coding, this combo covers the vast majority of your work — solid code quality, fast responses, low cost. Flip to Opus 4.8 or High/Max effort only when a problem genuinely demands it.
